<item>
	<title>Will It Ever be Normal by MyCreation [R]</title>
	<link>http://www.siye.co.uk/siye/viewstory.php?sid=130221</link>
	<description>Four years after the War, Harry and Ginny are enjoying their first summer after marriage in a vacation. Their lives are slowly evened out after war with the help of friends and family. But the enemy is always lurking in shadows and Will it ever be normal for the Potters.</description>
	<pubDate>Thu, 08 Feb 2018 11:55:34 -0500</pubDate><guid>http://www.siye.co.uk/siye/viewstory.php?sid=130221&amp;chapter=4</guid></item>
<item>
	<title>Some Cuts Leave Scars by melindaleo [PG-13]</title>
	<link>http://www.siye.co.uk/siye/viewstory.php?sid=130246</link>
	<description>Not all wounds heal completely – many scars aren’t readily visible. Join Harry and his friends as they journey through the year following the war, learning how to maneuver over hurdles both unique and lingering. An 8th-year sequel to the summer of These Cuts I Have.</description>
	<pubDate>Thu, 08 Feb 2018 09:01:07 -0500</pubDate><guid>http://www.siye.co.uk/siye/viewstory.php?sid=130246&amp;chapter=6</guid></item>
<item>
	<title>Fires of Time by GHL [PG]</title>
	<link>http://www.siye.co.uk/siye/viewstory.php?sid=130225</link>
	<description> &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;All space and time is relative.  The only constant is the speed of... fire.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Victory in tatters; great deeds undone; the world is unraveling, and Ginny has vanished.  Yet somehow, with the shared strengths of a cadre of highly implausible allies, Harry finds the will to persist through a bewildering tangle of centuries and realities, all hurtling toward an explosive, time-bending eruption.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;An impossibly charring sequel to the utterly fractious &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.siye.co.uk/viewstory.php?sid=129984&quot;&gt;Splinters&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
	<pubDate>Mon, 05 Feb 2018 10:04:12 -0500</pubDate><guid>http://www.siye.co.uk/siye/viewstory.php?sid=130225&amp;chapter=15</guid></item>
<item>
	<title>Framed by MichiganMuggle [R]</title>
	<link>http://www.siye.co.uk/siye/viewstory.php?sid=130253</link>
	<description>With Voldemort dead, Harry Potter is training to be an Auror and is finally back together with Ginny Weasley. But when a young woman dies of poisoning at the Ministry’s Midsummer Ball, Harry is the first suspect, and he can only uncover the true murderer by working with his childhood rival, Draco Malfoy.</description>
	<pubDate>Mon, 05 Feb 2018 05:50:26 -0500</pubDate><guid>http://www.siye.co.uk/siye/viewstory.php?sid=130253&amp;chapter=3</guid></item>
<item>
	<title>Milestones by 321jump [G]</title>
	<link>http://www.siye.co.uk/siye/viewstory.php?sid=130254</link>
	<description>A selection of one-shots, told from Ginny&apos;s POV and focusing on the lives of her and Harry directly after the battle. Kind of a follow on to my one-shot &apos;Silence&apos;, but it&apos;s not necessary to read that one first.</description>
